					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex of the 15th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper codex. </support>
								<extent>191 folios<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>280</height>
										<width>210</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>220</height>
										<width>165</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>191 folios (+1 modern paper flyleaf at the beginning and 1 at the end). </p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>19 quires of 10 leaves each. </p>
									<p>Signed with Hebrew letters at the end and at the beginning of a quire. </p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Paper much damaged. </p>
									<p>Stained. </p>
									<p>Slightly worm-eaten. </p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="2" ruledLines="29" writtenLines="29">
									<p>First folios supplied much later. </p>
									<p>Hard-point ruling visible. </p>
									<p>Catchwords on every verso. </p>
									<p>Uniform layout. Words in the last lines have occasionally elongated letters to fill the space. </p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Yemenite semi-cursive script of the 15th century. <name type="person" role="scribe">Hibah ben Ḥarun</name>
							</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole">: inscribed, folio 191v. </handNote>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>Folio 191v contains a record of death of <name type="person">[...] Yitsḥaḳ ibn Dan</name>, dated 1895 (1584), and a record of birth, <name type="person">Yitsḥaḳ ben Se῾adyah</name>, dated <date calendar="Seleucid">1896 </date>(<date calendar="Gregorian">1585</date>).</p>
						</additions>
